    "description": [
      "Featured on the TODAY Show, as one of Money Magazine's \"Freshest Money Apps and Websites,\" and as ABC News \"App of the Week.\" Manilla is the \"must-have\" free and secure financial life organization and reminder app that helps you simplify and organize your finances, bills, accounts and daily life in one place. Manilla also sends automatic bill pay reminders so that you'll never pay a late fee again. Manilla is owned by Hearst Corporation.ACCOLADES:\n * Money Magazine: Freshest Money Apps & Websites\n * ABCNEWs.com: App of the Week\n * PC Magazine: Top 100 Web Businesses\n * Winner, 2012 Webby Awards (Best Banking/Bill Pay Service & People's Voice)\n * The Today Show: \"It's genius!\"ACCOUNT MANAGER & BILL ORGANIZER\n- Everything in one place\n- Securely manage and monitor all your bills, finances, travel rewards & subscriptions\n- Automatic reminders to help you avoid late fees\n- Organized document storage for bills, statements, notices & offers\n- Single password log inSEE ALL OF YOUR ACCOUNTS\nManilla supports more than 3,000 leading providers and is adding more each week, making bill management easier than ever. With our new Custom Accounts feature, you can manage any account, like your rent, your babysitter, your cleaning service—you name it, you can manage it on Manilla.ALWAYS KNOW WHAT YOU OWE\nManilla will send you a text message or email to tell you when it’s time to pay your bills. With Manilla as your bill reminder, you’ll never miss a due date or pay a late fee again.GET FREE ONLINE DOCUMENT STORAGE\nDownload, print, email and read your documents whenever you want. We store it for you so no more searching for documents.STAY PROTECTED\nAt Manilla, your security is our number one priority. Manilla has top-level security and is monitored 24/7 for your protection. Manilla does not store passwords or secure information on your phone. Manilla's practices are verified by TRUSTe, VeriSign, McAfee, and other leading security agencies.BACKED BY HEARST CORPORATION\nManilla is a part of Hearst Corporation, one of the largest diversified communications companies in the world. Hearst is the owner of more than 300 magazines worldwide, including Esquire, Cosmopolitan, Marie Claire, Good Housekeeping, Popular Mechanics and Elle.PRAISE FOR MANILLA\n“I tested Manilla ahead of its introduction and found that the process of linking and managing a bill was simple. “ –New York Times\n“…[Manilla] delivers alerts, handles statements and payments, and provides a simple management interface…” –CNET\n\"It’s genius!” – The Today Show\nWinner of the 2012 Webby Award and People’s Voice Award for Best Banking/Bill Pay ServiceGETTING STARTED IS QUICK & EASY\n- Download the Manilla app\n- Securely link your account providers\n- Automatically see account balances and receive reminders and alerts"
    ],
